    {
      "id": "d2ed937109be8713ca00c4f65259aa65a92f244b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 454,
        "name": "Artem Blagodarenko",
        "email": "ablagodarenko@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "ablagodarenko"
      },
      "date": "2014-12-29 09:28:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI move here some comments from Andreas Dilger and wangdi they wrote to http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/13189/1 \n\n1)Some minor style issues that could be fixed if patch needs to be refreshed for some reason.\nlustre/lmv/lmv_obd.c\nLine 1867:\n(style) seems there should be an extra space here so '*' will align.\nLine 1874:\n(style) \"else\" should also have {} when \"if does\nLine 1875:\n(typo) s/sever/server/\n\nOk. I will fix this in next patch set.\n\n2) Andreas Dilger: What happens with a new client if a 2.5 client tries \"mkdir -i\" on a master (2.7.0) server (i.e. sends RPC to the master/wrong MDT)? Is the LASSERT() still there or was it removed in master? Does the MDT send the request to the right MDT?\n\nwangdi: Hmm, the new server (>=2.6) should be able to deal with the request from the create request from the Old client, i.e. the master (or 2.6) MDT can create the remote directory whether it is from new client (sending to salve MDT) or from old client (sending to master MDT). I remember we did that test when 2.6 release. Unfortunately we did not try new client with old server.\n\n+1. I have seen, there is no such LASSERT on  >= 2.6 servers. No problem with Old_client -> New severs compatibility.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1b74c933711affb3d07bfc4749c07496e84eedb3",
      "author": {
